Summary: We propose to measure transit times and durations, characterize TESS's growing sample of multiplanet systems, and identify targets for follow-up observations using data from Cycle 5 and earlier cycles. In addition, we identify multi-planet targets for Cycle 5 that merit 20-second cadence. These will provide the most accurate and precise constraints on transit durations and mid-transit times and will improve measurements of orbital periods, eccentricities, and impact parameters. These in turn further constrain planet radius, and variations in the transit times and/or durations help characterize planetary masses and orbits.
